  "description": "Built for an easy night meal, the recipe focuses on soft textures, digestibility, and controlled portions of whole grains. Kambu Roti with Ridge Gourd Kootu brings a distinct structure, seasoning pattern, and grain-legume balance to the table.",
  "preparation": "",
  "cooking_steps": [
    "Cook the vegetable with a splash of water on medium heat until just tender, then add the cooked dal and coconut paste and simmer 5 minutes on low heat.",
    "Temper the kootu with oil and curry leaves.",
    "Divide the dough into 4 balls, roll each into a thin roti, and cook on a hot tawa over medium-high heat for 1 minute per side until brown spots appear.",
    "Serve the rotis hot with the soft kootu."
  ],
